Ok, I know there are PLENTY of Iceworld remakes. But, frankly they all suck. This one doesn't. It acually is worth playing. It gets decent frame rate. And because of the buildings it changs up gameplay.

There are 2 error's though. In the txt file where it tell's the objectives, there is a spelling error. Also, one of the lights in the building is too low and is off the ceiling a bit. Nothign that changes gameplay, or seriously ruins the map.

This is probably the only decent iceworld.... since iceworld itself.

EDIT: There over 64 spawns I think. I haven't played with the full amount of people. It was made to have as many spawns as there are going to be players in the server.

Arpley Rail Bridge :: Created by nay0r

http://www.map-central.co.uk

Here I bring you fy_arpley which started out roughly 4/5 months ago, it is based of a real location as i
like to build from real places, although parts of the map like the sewers are made up from other sources and my own 
ideas, The map has come along way with countless compiles changing and fixing various parts of the map 

The map contains a few custom textures and also a few upgraded textures which i have made bump map textures for and ive also tweaked a few to enhance the look of the map. 

The soundscape is custom and is based around the official source maps, However the nav is just a basic auto generated 
one, this is because i thought it was good enough and didnt really need to the hassle of tweaking it.

Finally the map has HDR and LDR compiled and a fully working radar image including an underground layout on top.

The main part of the map is acutally quite small to fit the fy theme but i decided to build a few routes linking underground to suite rushers and to try and prevent a fest of snipering, so you really do need to be wise if your going to sniper and 
watch your backs.

Theres also one hidden scout contained in the map which I wont give the location away.

This is a map based on the Armory from Metal Gear Solid 1.  Due to my inability to make custom textures, I have made this a "VR" map for simplification.  There are 6 people on each team.  Essentially this is an FY map, but since there are many hiding places, terrorists can plant the bomb to make the round end more smoothly.  

There are 6 rooms.  All the doors are facing south.  In the upper left room, there is an autosniper.  In the upper middle room, there are FAMAS and one machinegun.  In the upper right room, there are 2 shotguns.  In the lower left room, there is an MP5 and LOTS of grenades.  In the lower middle room, there are various pistols.  In the lower right room, there are FAMAS.  The Ts get the advantage of being able to secure weapons first, so the CTs get some flashes to prevent fast rushing.  There are also pits that cause automatic deaths, just like in MGS1.  

This map has some lighting, but mp_flashlight 1 should be turned on.  There is a buyzone in the middle of the map.

Please leave a message if you have any comments or criticism.

   3. Start Counter-Strike: Source or your server.
